      ],
      "id": "9500f481-79a8-4371-8b08-20170e4eaad9",
      "name": "Sticky Note7"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# X Posting\n\n\n\n🔑 Get Twitter API Access\n1. https://developer.twitter.com → Create App\n2. Keys & Tokens tab → copy:\n   Client ID + Client Secret (OAuth2)\n3. n8n → Credentials → Twitter OAuth2\n   → paste → Connect\n   Save as \"X account\"\n\n",
        "height": 464,
        "width": 624
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        608,
        2176
      ],
      "id": "3bc6f943-4903-4c11-b1ee-13ff66bf9089",
      "name": "Sticky Note8"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🔑 How to Get LinkedIn Access Token\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nSTEP 1 — Create LinkedIn App\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n1. Go to https://linkedin.com/developers/apps\n2. Click \"Create App\"\n3. Fill in App Name, LinkedIn Page, Logo\n4. Click \"Create App\"\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nSTEP 2 — Add Scopes\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n1. Go to \"Products\" tab\n2. Request access for:\n   • Share on LinkedIn\n   • Sign In with LinkedIn using OpenID\n3. Wait for approval (usually instant)\n4. Go to \"Auth\" tab → confirm these scopes appear:\n   w_member_social, r_liteprofile, openid, profile, email\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nSTEP 3 — Get Your Token\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n1. Go to https://www.linkedin.com/developers/tools/oauth/token-generator\n2. Select your App from dropdown\n3. Tick all scopes: openid, profile, email,\n   w_member_social, r_liteprofile\n4. Click \"Request access token\"\n5. Log in with your LinkedIn account if asked\n6. Copy the token shown — starts with AQV...\n\n⚠️ Token lasts 60 days\n⚠️ Save it somewhere safe — you cannot see it again\n⚠️ After 60 days repeat Step 3 to get a new token\n\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nSTEP 4 — Put Token in n8n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nHeader Auth credential:\n1. n8n → Credentials → New → \"Header Auth\"\n2. Name:  Authorization\n   Value: Bearer <paste token here>\n3. Save as \"Header Auth account\"\n",
        "height": 976,
        "width": 624
      },
